  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b6198cdbfb3ab42799698812d172dc50, type: 3}
  m_Name: Fossegrim
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ISUGameDev.SpearGame.Dialogue.Dialogue
  dialogueStrings:
  - Well, well, well. Who do we have here?
  - A Valkyrie? All on her lonesome?
  - It must be a lonely path fighting for the 9 realms. No company, no conversation,
    no fun.
  - "Why don\u2019t you take a rest in the sea with me? Take a little weight off
    of those heroic shoulders of yours."
  - Not today, spirit. You cannot fool me.
  - I know you well. Your waters are a danger and I am not so easily charmed into
    my own demise.
  - "Oh come on! You\u2019re no fun."
  - Fine. Run along if you must.
  - Actually, you may be of use to me.
  - What do you know of Ragnarok?
  - Ragnarok? Is that why you are so eager to pass me by?
  - "Hm\u2026Well I suppose I cannot have my fun if the world ends can I?"
  - "Yes\u2026I suppose I can tell you what I have seen."
  - Loki has heard of you and your quest, though I do not know many who have not
    at this point.
  - He has begun building forces in Muspelheim just for little old you!
  - "And\u2026everyone else I imagine. Hahaha! End of the world and all!"
  - You know, the fun thing about Muspelheim is that its fires caused Ymir to be
    formed in the beginning.
  - Where streams of ice and fire met, Ymir rose out of melting frost.
  - How very dramatic.
  - All of that to say, I believe that may be why Loki has found himself there.
  - "The secrets of how to free Surtr may very well be intertwined with him and his
    brother\u2019s origins."
  - Hence why Loki is there.
  - However, beyond that I know nothing more.
  - Thank you.
  - Do not cause too much trouble, spirit.
  - No promises, hero.
  characterIcon: {fileID: 0}
  characterName: Fossegrim
